00:13:42,150 --> 00:13:43,560
and that's all the service is doing.

355
00:13:43,560 --> 00:13:45,840
We collect all these inputs from you

356
00:13:45,840 --> 00:13:48,000
and take care of the deployment.

357
00:13:48,000 --> 00:13:50,070
It is a fully self-managed service

358
00:13:50,070 --> 00:13:51,840
minus the initial deployment.

359
00:13:51,840 --> 00:13:55,800
We wanted to kind of remove
that deployment from you

360
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:58,470
and take care of it on behalf of you.

361
00:13:58,470 --> 00:14:00,270
So when the stack is deployed,

362
00:14:00,270 --> 00:14:03,527
you get all these components
deployed, from SDDC manager

363
00:14:03,527 --> 00:14:07,440
to the ESXI hypervisor,
to storage, to networking.

364
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:08,700
But we also take care,

365
00:14:08,700 --> 00:14:11,760
and as you'll see when we talk
about the building blocks,

366
00:14:11,760 --> 00:14:14,700
the underlying connectivity
and storage options for you,

367
00:14:14,700 --> 00:14:18,750
depending on your use case
and your application needs.

368
00:14:18,750 --> 00:14:20,850
When we deploy the stack,

369
00:14:20,850 --> 00:14:23,520
we deploy it in a single
consolidated domain.

370
00:14:23,520 --> 00:14:25,470
But of course there's flexibility for you

371
00:14:25,470 --> 00:14:27,690
as you deploy more hosts

372
00:14:27,690 --> 00:14:29,730
and you can bring up additional clusters,

373
00:14:29,730 --> 00:14:32,163
you can do multiple workload domains.

374
00:14:34,440 --> 00:14:36,927
We deploy, I kept saying we deploy,

375
00:14:36,927 --> 00:14:39,570
EVS service deploys
the environment for you

376
00:14:39,570 --> 00:14:43,410
in your AWS account in
a VPC that you choose.

