00:15:03,150 --> 00:15:05,040
We also take care of capacity for you.

384
00:15:05,040 --> 00:15:08,100
So you place in a capacity
request reservation

385
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:12,390
saying, "Hey, I need 10
hosts by a specific date."

386
00:15:12,390 --> 00:15:16,020
And we enable that
capacity into your account.

387
00:15:16,020 --> 00:15:18,540
But anything upward of the hyper wise

388
00:15:18,540 --> 00:15:21,990
of the ESXI stack upwards
is your responsibility.

389
00:15:21,990 --> 00:15:23,430
This means you are responsible

390
00:15:23,430 --> 00:15:25,320
for patching your environment,

391
00:15:25,320 --> 00:15:27,963
you're responsible for updates, et cetera.

392
00:15:30,420 --> 00:15:33,450
There's three key building
blocks that I kept mentioning.

