00:15:33,450 --> 00:15:35,703
The first one obviously is compute.

394
00:15:36,570 --> 00:15:41,040
We started with i4i.metal
as our first instance type.

395
00:15:41,040 --> 00:15:42,600
This is a bare metal instance

396
00:15:42,600 --> 00:15:45,270
where we deploy the environment on.

397
00:15:45,270 --> 00:15:48,510
We have a good history with i4i.metal.

398
00:15:48,510 --> 00:15:49,920
For some of you who are familiar

399
00:15:49,920 --> 00:15:53,430
with the VMware cloud on
AWS, the managed service,

400
00:15:53,430 --> 00:15:55,350
we utilized i4i.metal.

401
00:15:55,350 --> 00:15:57,990
We've received good
feedback from customers

402
00:15:57,990 --> 00:16:01,143
across various use cases
of their applications.

403
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:05,490
These instances also go
through a full certification

404
00:16:05,490 --> 00:16:06,323
with Broadcom.

405
00:16:06,323 --> 00:16:09,690
So today, if you go into the
Broadcom Compatibility Guide,

406
00:16:09,690 --> 00:16:14,640
you will see Amazon i4i.metal
listed as a certified instance

407
00:16:14,640 --> 00:16:16,980
to run VCF 5.2.1.

408
00:16:16,980 --> 00:16:19,860
So we do go through the
entire service certification,

409
00:16:19,860 --> 00:16:22,773
storage and network
certification with Broadcom.

410
00:16:24,930 --> 00:16:26,730
We launched with one instance type

411
00:16:26,730 --> 00:16:29,820
and our goal is eventually
to get every metal instance

412
00:16:29,820 --> 00:16:33,390
that's available on the AWS
portfolio available for you

413
00:16:33,390 --> 00:16:34,627
so you can choose based on,

414
00:16:34,627 --> 00:16:37,500
"Hey, I do have a high-memory workload

