00:17:54,930 --> 00:17:56,490
which gives a better performance

443
00:17:56,490 --> 00:17:59,130
compared to the OSA architecture.

444
00:17:59,130 --> 00:18:03,000
So vSAN forms the primary
storage that is available.

445
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:05,850
What we've also had
feedback from customers

446
00:18:05,850 --> 00:18:08,160
is, "Hey, I wanna make
sure this is consistent

